gomodel:SYNGO_4035  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 8 B and C: Immunoelectron microscopy demonstrate localisation of NPYR1 on dense-core vesicles. (thin black arrows mark the immunoreaction product, while DCVs are separately labelled)\n\nThe paper comments on specificity tests for the antibody used against NPYR1 by staining it on WT and NPY KO mice. However, the data wasn't shown. The rabbit NPY antibody was produced referred from Stanic et al., 2011. (PMID 21452195). Experimental description: male Sprague-Dawley rats were used" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
